<h1>Location Groups</h1>

<p>
Location Groups allow administrators to logically group locations together for easier
management, reporting, and configuration. This document explains how to create and
manage Location Groups.
</p>

<h2>Overview</h2>
<p>
Location Groups help organizations manage multiple locations efficiently by grouping
related locations under a single entity.
</p>

<img src="images/image1.png" alt="Location Groups Overview">

<h2>Creating a Location Group</h2>
<ol>
  <li>Navigate to <strong>Settings â†’ Location Groups</strong>.</li>
  <li>Click <strong>Create New Location Group</strong>.</li>
  <li>Enter a name and description.</li>
  <li>Select the locations you want to associate.</li>
  <li>Click <strong>Save</strong>.</li>
</ol>

<img src="images/image2.png" alt="Create Location Group">

<h2>Editing a Location Group</h2>
<ol>
  <li>Select an existing Location Group.</li>
  <li>Click <strong>Edit</strong>.</li>
  <li>Modify the details or assigned locations.</li>
  <li>Click <strong>Update</strong>.</li>
</ol>

<img src="images/image3.png" alt="Edit Location Group">

<h2>Deleting a Location Group</h2>
<p>
To delete a Location Group:
</p>
<ol>
  <li>Select the Location Group.</li>
  <li>Click <strong>Delete</strong>.</li>
  <li>Confirm the deletion.</li>
</ol>

<img src="images/image4.png" alt="Delete Location Group">

<h2>Important Notes</h2>
<ul>
  <li>Deleting a Location Group does not delete the locations.</li>
  <li>Users must have appropriate permissions.</li>
  <li>Changes take effect immediately.</li>
</ul>

